{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Linear Steps with Background Crawl\n      Wizard stays linear (Step 1 → 2 → 3 → ...) but the crawl kicks off after Step 2 (Website) and runs silently in the background. Steps 3-6 are the new questions (Goals → Personas → Keywords → Competitors). A subtle progress bar at the top shows crawl status. When the user reaches Competitors, AI suggestions are ready.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Simple mental model — user just clicks \"Next\"\n            Reuses existing stepper component\n            Each step has clear validation before advancing\n            Crawl completion is invisible, no context-switching\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            If user is fast, they may reach Competitors before crawl finishes\n            6 steps feels long — may increase drop-off\n            Steps 3-5 (Goals/Personas/Keywords) are lightweight — could feel padded","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1773272278285}
